main event: On 23 September 1954, a bright object was observed moving vertically and horizontally, with a smaller object orbiting around a larger one. The observers, Mr. and Mrs. R.E. Case, described it as similar to a brightly lit star or planet.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 1 minute.
The object had characteristics of both vertical and horizontal movement, with a small object rotating in a circular orbit around a larger one.
The report mentions that there was insufficient data to evaluate the case.
The observers described the object as appearing similar to a brightly lit star or planet, with visible exhaust, but the description was inconclusive.
Despite a clear night and detailed wind and weather conditions, there were no definitive conclusions drawn about the nature of the sighting.
sighted object: Bright object with a smaller one orbiting around it
